Izzat Ibrahim al-Douri died in fighting with government troops near Tikrit on Friday . 
  His body was today delivered to the Ministry of Health in Baghdad in a glass coffin . 
  He was deputy to Saddam and ranked sixth on US military's list of the 55 most-wanted Iraqis after the invasion of Iraq in 2003 . 
  Al-douri was reportedly working alongside ISIS militants in Tikrit . 
  He had a $10m bounty on his head and was the 'King of Clubs' in the infamous pack of cards . 
 